<p>The Chemistry Department is not accepting applications at this time.&nbsp; Please check back when registration begins for next semester.</p>
<!-- END NOT ACCEPTING APPLICATIONS -->
<p></p>
<!-- ACCEPTING APPLICATIONS: Disable when not accepting applications. --  >
<p><strong>Thank you for your interest in applying to work in the Chemistry Department</strong></p>
<p>Please keep the following in mind as you apply:</p>
<ul>
<li>Please make sure you meet the credit requirements for working on campus (<a href="x33473.xml">see Student Employment F.A.Q.</a>)</li>
<li>Even if you have applied to the Chemistry Department previously, if you would like to be considered for the upcoming semester you will need to apply again.&nbsp; Applications from past semesters are not kept on file.</li>
<li>Please have your class schedule at hand, after you fill out the application you will be asked about class schedule and when you are available to work.
<ul>
<li>&nbsp;<em>If you have not registered yet, please do not apply until you have registered for your classes and have a class schedule.</em></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Depending on when you apply and when the department begins to fill the open positions, it may be a few weeks before you hear back about your application. You <em>will</em>be contacted regarding your application.
<ul>
<li>&nbsp; We allow time for students to register and apply before considering the applications.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>Please fill out the <a href="https://creator.zoho.com/lawrence.chem/chemistry-application/form-perma/Application/bB7wRQPBWyAzBtefM7wxaDHS25jdWaBqSRu77jFVRwYa874dXpCQ0h4Z0fXaZZEVP6rwUAfQHVP3jGf5YxTxPaV2Hzhp56KrtdWz/">Chemistry Student Employment Application</a> when you are ready to apply.</p>
<p></p>
<p>If you have questions about when you can work with less than 12 credits please contact the <a href="mailto:humanresources@byui.edu">Student Employment Office</a> or <a href="mailto:lawrencebr@byui.edu" target="_self">Brad Lawrence</a>.</p>
